LamstarOutputLayer

public LamstarOutputLayer(java.util.TreeSet<org.artificial_neural_networks.common.Classification> recognizedClasses,
                          java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Long[]> inputLayerMap,
                          java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Long,java.lang.Long[]> correlationLayerMap,
                          double pReward,
                          double pPunish)
                   throws org.artificial_neural_networks.exceptions.NotEnoughClassesException,
                          org.artificial_neural_networks.exceptions.NotEnoughNeuronsException
The default constructor of a LAMSTAR Output Layer

Parameters:
recognizedClasses - A set containing all the classes that must be recognized
inputLayerMap - the keys are the IDs of the input layers and the values are the IDs of the neurons contained in the corresponding input layer
correlationLayerMap - the keys are the IDs of the correlation layers and the values are the IDs of the neurons contained in the corresponding correlation layer
pReward - the amount by which reward a neuron
pPunish - the amount by which punish a neuron
Throws:
org.artificial_neural_networks.exceptions.NotEnoughClassesException - the first parameter has less than 2 classes
org.artificial_neural_networks.exceptions.NotEnoughNeuronsException - the input or correlation map contains a number of neurons that is less than 1
